commit_list.message: Fixed a problem in which the run stack (step tree) was occasionally built improperly.  This fixes the display of some negative Other values.
Updated CONTRIBUTORS file to reference recent pull from bryanl.
Added an unobtrusive link to Manage product page.  Removed some debug output.
Added styling for the Back to Run link.
Only require a user to signup if they want to share a run (privately or publicly).
Improved description of the 'render partial' step for Rails 2.1 PartialTemplate#render calls.
Instrument ActionView::PartialTemplate#render under Rails 2.1.  Don't attempt to load instrumentation modules for classes that are not relevant in a specific version of Rails.
Fixed TextMate links to be xhtml strict 1.0 compliant (use & instead of & in anchor href urls with params).
Toggle display of sql explain element using sandboxed TuneUp javascript.
Fix partial instrumentation for apps running on Rails 2.1.  Fix duplicate rendered partials under Rails 2.0.2 and earlier.
Specify explicit file extensions for rendered partials.
Explicitly specify '*.html.erb' when rendering partials.  Filter :password param when writing to tuneup.log.
Change 'Upload this Run' to 'Share this Run'.
Updated CHANGELOG and Manifest files.  Updated plugin version to v0.8.7.  Removed History.rdoc file in favor of CHANGELOG.
Write the tuneup.log to the RAILS_ROOT/log dir.
Handle valid content types other than text/html (like strict XHTML with content type application/xhmtl+xml).  Added CHANGELOG. Updated Manifest.

Remove tuneup logger.
Abstract filter name extraction.
Updated README with supported browser and rails versions.
Handle situation where there were no previous runs.
Add application name to the Run environment.
Send environment data with the stack info.
Consider get_api_key request as successful if response code is 200..299
Install task now creates a basic config/fiveruns_tuneup.yml file.  Uninstall task removes it.
Start Dash after application classes are loaded.
